{
  "type": "feat",
  "name": "Silver Shears",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><span class=\"va-quotation-text\"><em>The flowing waters of the Mithral Current feed your Intoxicating Petals.</em></span></p><p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Two @UUID[Compendium.pf1-pow.disciplines.Item.iwfbEXyacCnVLEoH]{Intoxicating Petal} maneuvers, two @UUID[Compendium.pf1-pow.disciplines.Item.12RYyhGvq0VoWIiv]{Mithral Curren}t maneuvers</p><p><strong>Benefit:</strong> When you initiate an iaijutsu strike (one which has an additional effect if you draw your weapon as part of initiating the strike) while maintaining an Intoxicating Petal stance, you may also choose to tear a number of sprouts off of your foe equal to 1/2 the strike's level (rounded up). You tear off sprouts before inflicting sprout using this attack, if any.</p><p>As long as you maintain a Mithral Current stance, if you draw your weapon as part of initiating an Intoxicating Petal strike you may choose to apply [sprout 1] to the target(s) on a successful hit or failed saving throw using that maneuver.</p>",
      "instructions": ""
    },
